I shall venture to say that the above error is looking like a classical jar shadowing problem. I am not sure when you are getting this, as you have not mentioned it, is it during compilation, testing or WAR deployment (my guess would be compilation/test).

The problem most likely stems from jersey-container-servlet-core getting included transitively. It declares a provided dependency on servlet API 2.4 which does not have the &#39;getStatus()&#39; method defined (Refer: [this post][1]).

If 2.4 is on classpath, this will shadow (come before in path search) other jars containing javax.servlet package and it does not have the method required.

Also refer [aspects of Maven dependency scope][2]. Refer [this post][3], as to why this might not be turning up on the &#39;dependency:tree&#39;.

One way out is to force use of the servlet jar above 2.4 (like 3.0, 3.01, ...) with a &#39;dependencyManagement&#39; element in your pom and mention the version required.

Added this section wrt the comments
===================================

Try adding a &#39;dependencyManagement&#39; element to force the version:

    &lt;project&gt;
        &lt;dependencyManagement&gt;
           &lt;dependencies&gt;
               &lt;dependency&gt;
                    &lt;groupId&gt;javax.servlet&lt;/groupId&gt;
                    &lt;artifactId&gt;3.0.1&lt;/artifactId&gt;
                    &lt;version&gt;3.0.1&lt;/version&gt;
                    &lt;scope&gt;provided&lt;/scope&gt;
               &lt;/dependency&gt;
           &lt;/dependencies&gt;
       &lt;/dependencyManagement&gt;
       &lt;dependencies&gt;&lt;!-- Your current dependencies --&gt;&lt;/dependencies&gt;
    &lt;/project&gt;




  [1]: https://stackoverflow.com/questions/44730096/javax-servlet-http-httpservletresponse-getstatus-not-found
  [2]: https://maven.apache.org/guides/introduction/introduction-to-dependency-mechanism.html#Transitive_Dependencies
  [3]: https://stackoverflow.com/questions/48874990/maven-transitive-dependencies-with-provided-scope

